            questions: [
                { passage: "The smartphone is a convenient and essential part of our personal and business lives. But is it secure if its lost or stolen? Not likely. Here's another twist: Even if you've got the phone in your hand, it may not be safe.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "The smartphone is a convenient and essential part of our personal and business lives." }, { label: "B", text: "But is it secure if its lost or stolen?" }, { label: "C", text: "Not likely." }, { label: "D", text: "Even if you've got the phone in your hand, it may not be safe." }], a: 1, explain: "B is incorrect: 'its' should be 'it's' (it is) — 'it's lost or stolen' is required here." },
                { passage: "Steve McCoy was 20 years old when his wife, Michelle, gave birth to their first children – a son named Leroy. It was 1996. McCoy was living in the tiny town of Cherokee, North Carolina. He was the first member of his family to go to college.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "Steve McCoy was 20 years old when his wife, Michelle, gave birth to their first children – a son named Leroy." }, { label: "B", text: "It was 1996." }, { label: "C", text: "McCoy was living in the tiny town of Cherokee, North Carolina." }, { label: "D", text: "He was the first member of his family to go to college." }], a: 0, explain: "A is incorrect: 'children' should be 'child' — only one child (a single son named Leroy) was born." },
                { passage: "The 1918 flu pandemic fueled many scientific advances, including the discovery of the influenza virus. However, the virus itself did not caused all of the deaths. Instead, a fraction of individuals infected by the virus were susceptible to pneumonia due to secondary infection by bacteria. In an era before antibiotics, pneumonia could be fatal.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "The 1918 flu pandemic fueled many scientific advances, including the discovery of the influenza virus." }, { label: "B", text: "However, the virus itself did not caused all of the deaths." }, { label: "C", text: "Instead, a fraction of individuals infected by the virus were susceptible to pneumonia due to secondary infection by bacteria." }, { label: "D", text: "In an era before antibiotics, pneumonia could be fatal." }], a: 1, explain: "B is incorrect: 'did not caused' should be 'did not cause' — after 'did not', the base form of the verb is required." },
                { passage: "In 2014, Scottish artist Katie Paterson started a new project – one that will ultimately last a century and rely solely on hope and the goodness of future generations. That project, called the Future Library, now well underway. It will result in an anthology of 100 books, printed 100 years in the future, with paper from trees out of a newly planted forest in Norway.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "In 2014, Scottish artist Katie Paterson started a new project –" }, { label: "B", text: "one that will ultimately last a century and rely solely on hope and the goodness of future generations." }, { label: "C", text: "That project, called the Future Library, now well underway." }, { label: "D", text: "It will result in an anthology of 100 books, printed 100 years in the future, with paper from trees out of a newly planted forest in Norway." }], a: 2, explain: "C is incorrect: 'now well underway' is a sentence fragment missing a verb. It should be 'is now well underway'." },
                { passage: "Migration is costly. It's costly in economic terms, and it's costly in terms of life disruption. It's not something done light. Immigrants move because they perceive an opportunity to better themselves in some way.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "Migration is costly." }, { label: "B", text: "It's costly in economic terms, and it's costly in terms of life disruption." }, { label: "C", text: "It's not something done light." }, { label: "D", text: "Immigrants move because they perceive an opportunity to better themselves in some way." }], a: 2, explain: "C is incorrect: 'done light' should be 'done lightly' — an adverb is needed to modify the verb 'done'." },
                { passage: "Forget party parrots: When it comes to avian noise-making, crested pigeons are the real party animal. If you've ever heard a flock frantically get airborne, you're probably familiar with the loud, high-pitched whistle they make during takeoff. But you may be surprised to learn that the sound doesn't come from their beaks – it come from their wings.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "When it comes to avian noise-making, crested pigeons are the real party animal." }, { label: "B", text: "If you've ever heard a flock frantically get airborne, you're probably familiar with the loud, high-pitched whistle they make during takeoff." }, { label: "C", text: "But you may be surprised to learn that the sound doesn't come from their beaks –" }, { label: "D", text: "it come from their wings." }], a: 3, explain: "D is incorrect: 'it come' should be 'it comes' — third-person singular present requires the 's'." },
                { passage: "In 1869, Antoinette Brown Blackwell published her first book. She sent a copy to Charles Darwin, whose Origin of Species had taken the world by storm a decade earlier. Darwin replied at Blackwell personally, thanking her for her book. Darwin made one mistake in his response, though: His letter was addressed, 'Dear Sir.'", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "In 1869, Antoinette Brown Blackwell published her first book." }, { label: "B", text: "She sent a copy to Charles Darwin, whose Origin of Species had taken the world by storm a decade earlier." }, { label: "C", text: "Darwin replied at Blackwell personally, thanking her for her book." }, { label: "D", text: "Darwin made one mistake in his response, though: His letter was addressed, 'Dear Sir.'" }], a: 2, explain: "C is incorrect: 'replied at' should be 'replied to' — the correct preposition for communicating back is 'to'." },
                { passage: "A German regulator has banned the sale of smartwatches aimed at children, describing them such as spying devices. It had previously banned an Internet-connected doll for similar reasons. The regulator urged parents who had such watches to destroy them. One expert said the decision could be a 'game-changer' for Internet-connected devices.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "A German regulator has banned the sale of smartwatches aimed at children, describing them such as spying devices." }, { label: "B", text: "It had previously banned an Internet-connected doll for similar reasons." }, { label: "C", text: "The regulator urged parents who had such watches to destroy them." }, { label: "D", text: "One expert said the decision could be a 'game-changer' for Internet-connected devices." }], a: 0, explain: "A is incorrect: 'describing them such as' should simply be 'describing them as'. 'Such as' is used for giving examples, not for descriptions." },
                { passage: "Elephants have a lower incidence of cancer than would be expected statistically, suggesting that they have evolved ways to protect itself against the disease. A new study reveals how elephants do it: An old gene that was no longer functional was recycled, enabling them to cull potentially cancerous cells early.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "Elephants have a lower incidence of cancer than would be expected statistically," }, { label: "B", text: "suggesting that they have evolved ways to protect itself against the disease." }, { label: "C", text: "A new study reveals how elephants do it:" }, { label: "D", text: "An old gene that was no longer functional was recycled, enabling them to cull potentially cancerous cells early." }], a: 1, explain: "B is incorrect: 'protect itself' should be 'protect themselves' — the plural subject 'they' (elephants) requires the plural reflexive pronoun." },
                { passage: "Newcomers to America, according to Eduardo Díaz, are always mindful of two homes: their community of residence (where they immigrated from) and their community of origin (where they emigrated from). To ignore that internal conflict would miss an opportunity to engage with what being an American immigrant truly entails.", parts: [{ label: "A", text: "Newcomers to America, according to Eduardo Díaz, are always mindful of two homes:" }, { label: "B", text: "their community of residence (where they immigrated from)" }, { label: "C", text: "their community of origin (where they emigrated from)." }, { label: "D", text: "To ignore that internal conflict would miss an opportunity to engage with what being an American immigrant truly entails." }], a: 1, explain: "B is incorrect: logically, the community of residence is where they immigrated TO, not from. Origin is where they emigrated from." }
            ]
